er that (at the time) ran $18 billion of outside money. =E2=80=9CThe invest=
ors in Pershing Square aren=E2=80=99t paying $1 billion for 10% of a firm t=
hat manages $18 billion,=E2=80=9D  I wrote. =E2=80=9CThey=E2=80=99re paying=
 $1 billion for 10% of a firm that they expect to manage more than twice th=
at in the near future, and to grow from there.=E2=80=9D They really want PS=
US to work out, because =E2=80=9CPershing Square will manage a lot more mon=
ey=E2=80=9D seems like a pretty important part of their thesis.


