<td class=3D"body-component__content" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; m=
so-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt; line-height: 150%; padding: 0 =
10px;">
<div id=3D"footnote-1" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[1] Also, if the IPO is 10 times covered =E2=
=80=94 there are orders for 1,000% of the shares =E2=80=94 investors will i=
nflate their orders to get an allocation. =E2=80=9CIf it=E2=80=99s 10x over=
subscribed, everyone will get allocated about 10% of the shares they want, =
so if I want a million shares I should put in an order for 10 million,=E2=
=80=9D is the rough thought process.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-2" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[2] A digression. I <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/36186471.204172/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJn=
LmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDctMTYvYmlsbC1hY2ttYW4tY2FuLXR3ZWV0LWh=
pcy1uZXctZnVuZD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNzI1MjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJn=
V0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA3MjUmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c=
3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC0d5efae7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">wrote last week</a> that=
 that $25 billion target was extremely ambitious, that it would be impossib=
le to achieve with just retail demand, and that it relied on Ackman being a=
ble to convince institutional equity managers that it was okay for them to =
invest their clients money in PSUS, which is, after all, another equity man=
ager=E2=80=99s fund. As I said: =E2=80=9CThere is a pitch to institutional =
stock investors, to asset managers, which is in part, sure, =E2=80=98this m=
ight trade at a premium because retail investors love me,=E2=80=99 but whic=
h is also in part =E2=80=98this is not a stock fund.=E2=80=99 If you are an=
 institutional stock investor, buying a stock that is just another stock in=
vestor=E2=80=99s fund is a weird move: You=E2=80=99re paying extra fees, an=
d you=E2=80=99re outsourcing the work of stock-picking to him. But buying a=
 stock that is a company =E2=80=94 that happens to be a company that invest=
s mostly in stocks =E2=80=94 is fine. Investing in Berkshire Hathaway is mo=
re socially acceptable than investing in ARKK.=E2=80=9D This was a tough pi=
tch, and apparently it got some pushback. Ackman <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/36186471.204172/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9B=
cmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzIwMDI2NjAvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTI0MTg0MjU2L2Q4MTM1NDBkZnd=
wLmh0bQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCe1f809cb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">wrote yesterday</a>: =E2=
=80=9CFor certain mutual funds, some hedge funds and certain other asset ma=
nagers, an important concern is whether PSUS fits their mandate as some per=
ceive PSUS as investing another manager=E2=80=99s investment vehicle. We ha=
ve addressed this issue by analogy by comparing PSUS to Berkshire Hathaway.=
 We make the case that if you can own Berkshire, an investment holding comp=
any that owns both controlling stakes in companies as well as public securi=
ties, then why should you not be able to invest in an investment holding co=
mpany that buys minority stakes in public companies at a discount with a pa=
th to control, in a company and with a tax-exempt corporate tax structure. =
The above argument wins the day for many investors, but not all. Some of th=
e largest mutual fund complexes have passed for this reason (e.g., the Capi=
tal Group Companies).=E2=80=9D</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-3" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[3] Ackman recently sold 10% of the management=
 company to investors at a $10 billion valuation, which, <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/36186471.204172/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxv=
b21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDYtMDYvYmlsbC1hY2ttYW4td2FudHM=
tYS1sb3Qtb2YteW91ci1tb25leT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNzI1MjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaX=
VtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA3MjUmdXRtX2NhbXBha=
WduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCbc111f04" itemprop=3D"StoryLink=
" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">I wrote</a>, =
seems pretty rich for an asset manager that (at the time) ran $18 billion o=
f outside money. =E2=80=9CThe investors in Pershing Square aren=E2=80=99t p=
aying $1 billion for 10% of a firm that manages $18 billion,=E2=80=9D  I wr=
ote. =E2=80=9CThey=E2=80=99re paying $1 billion for 10% of a firm that they=
 expect to manage more than twice that in the near future, and to grow from=
 there.=E2=80=9D They really want PSUS to work out, because =E2=80=9CPershi=
ng Square will manage a lot more money=E2=80=9D seems like a pretty importa=
nt part of their thesis.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
